  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed via Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary-condition variability and blood viscosity scatter; a screening sensitivity study is described in the UQ report narrative identifying shear-stress exposure time as a potentially influential parameter, but formal ranked sensitivity indices have not been separately linked as a structured analysis record.",
