      "name": "Grid convergence index study — three-level mesh refinement",
      "description": "Three mesh levels (2.1M, 6.4M, 14.8M elements) evaluated using Richardson extrapolation. GCI fine-grid < 2.1% for NIH QoI. Discretization error classified as negligible at the fine mesh level used for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cpb-uq-mc",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo UQ propagation — boundary condition and material property variability",
      "description": "500-sample Monte Carlo propagation of inlet flow rate (±5%), rotational speed (±1%), and blood dynamic viscosity (±12% population variability). Output NIH 95th-percentile interval reported. A screening sensitivity study referenced in the UQ report narrative suggests shear-stress exposure time dominates output variance, but ranked Sobol indices or other structured sensitivity metrics have not been formally computed or linked as a separate analysis artifact."
    }
