    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped to not-assessed per ASME V&V 40 MRL 2 requirements. Uncertainty quantification via Monte Carlo propagation completed and documented; output 95th-percentile NIH remains below regulatory threshold. The UQ report narrative references a screening sensitivity study suggesting shear-stress exposure time as the dominant variance driver; however, the assessment team judged that the MRL 2 threshold does not mandate formal ranked sensitivity indices, and the overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the Accepted decision for the CPB hemolysis COU.",
